## Plan Summary

**Bug:** Classic off-by-one error in `src/utils.ts` — `processItems` uses `i < items.length - 1` instead of `i < items.length`, so the loop always stops one iteration early.

**Fix:** A single character change on line 7 of `src/utils.ts`:

```typescript
// Before (buggy)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length - 1; i++) {

// After (fixed)
for (let i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
```

**Impact:** 2 Vitest tests currently fail (`"should process all items"` and `"should handle a single item"`). After the fix, all tests will pass. No other files need to be touched.

